CompanyDealMaster.DealDescription:
Cotemar SA de CV has selected SAP SE's SAP HANA, SAP Cloud Platform and SAP Fieldglass solutions. This contract was signed in the 4th quarter of SAP's FY2019, ending December 31, 2019.


Key Benefits:

By consolidating data onto a single platform, Cotemar is believed to have full visibility of their operations in real time, thereby allowing them to make better decisions. They will also transition to SAP Fieldglass solutions to more efficiently manage their external workforce.

Tata Consultancy Services Ltd. (TCS) has been selected as a strategic partner by Aptiv PLC, a global technology company to continue to advance their IT Infrastructure Operations by bringing in business aligned, scalable, secure, digitally automated operations using cognitive tools powered by the MFDM framework.

China Three Gorges Brasil Energia Ltda. (CTG Brasil) has selected SAP SE's SAP S/4HANA and SAP Ariba solutions to support their acquisition-centric growth plan. This contract was signed in the 4th quarter of SAP's FY2019, ending December 31, 2019.


Business Need:

CTG Brasil needed a solution to unify all new companies on one robust platform and gain access to real-time information and enable them to consolidate procurement operations and improve management for better decisions.

Fomento Economico Mexicano SAB de CV (FEMSA) has implemented SAP SE's SAP Ariba solutions to help consolidate their procurement processes to enable employees to make better buying decisions. This contract was signed in the 4th quarter of SAP's FY2019, ending December 31, 2019.

Michigan State University (MSU) has engaged with Oracle Corporation (Oracle) to replace their mainframe student information system infrastructure.


Contract Responsibilities:

Under this contract, MSU will be implementing Oracle's several Oracle Cloud solutions, including Oracle Student Financial Planning (SFP). They also selected Exadata Cloud at Customer to operate PeopleSoft Campus Solutions in one hybrid cloud environment.


Key Benefits:

This modernization project is believed to help MSU address challenges around fiscal sustainability, transforming the student experience and building capacity for long-term institutional innovation.

RingCentral Australia, subsidiary of RingCentral, has been chosen by Tritium Pty Ltd as its new global communications solution.


Business Requirement:

Tritium's offices in Australia, Netherlands, and United States each had a different voice-only legacy phone system, which did not support the constant inter-office and customer communication and collaboration needs of voice, video, online meetings, and messaging. Also, these legacy systems could not support the mobility needs of employees traveling throughout Asia-Pacific, Europe and the US. Hence, Tritium needed a global communications solution that could be centrally managed and maintained to improve operational efficiency and reduce overall costs. 


Contract Responsibilities:

As part of the contract, RingCentral Office solution provides voice, video, online meetings and team messaging to support the communications needs for Tritium’s employees worldwide. Tritium is now able to route calls from customers worldwide to the right account representative or technical engineer, dependent on their specific requirements, where they are located, and also taking into account their time zone.

Tata Consultancy Services Ltd. (TCS) has been selected by CSL Behring, a rare diseases biotech company, as a strategic business technology partner to help consolidate and transform its operations and business enablement model and support its accelerated growth plans.

Ithaca College (IC) will consolidate all of their applications with Oracle Corporation (Oracle) to operate on a single cloud platform. They are currently implementing Oracle's E-Business Suite and HCM Cloud solutions, and is expanding to automate and migrate their financial and planning functions to the cloud.


Key Benefits:

With the addition of Oracle Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) Cloud and Enterprise Performance Management (EPM) Cloud, IC expects to see an increase in staff and business efficiency, along with enhanced analysis, monitoring and management reporting throughout the planning and budgeting process.

Further, Oracle Cloud is also believed to enable them to streamline their operations to even better serve their students.

DePaul University will implement Oracle Corporation (Oracle)'s Oracle ERP Cloud and HCM Cloud and integrate them with their existing Oracle PeopleSoft Campus Solutions application. The interest to move to a modern system was based on the university's desire to adopt best practices for business processes, and new capabilities such as Artificial Intelligence (AI) and embedded intelligence to drive better efficiency and sustainability.
